President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Nebraska due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from June 1, 2010, onwards. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Stephen R. Thompson as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.